Installation:
   	git clone https://github.com/juliendz/dotvim.git ~/.vim


Create symlinks:
	ls -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
	ls -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Updating local .vim to latest changes:
	git pull
	git submodule init
	git submodule update
	
Windows:
	Copy gvimrc to $VIM/_vimrc


Remove submodule (plugin):
To remove a submodule you need to:
    Delete the relevant section from the .gitmodules file.
    Stage the .gitmodules changes git add .gitmodules
    Delete the relevant section from .git/config.
    Run git rm --cached path_to_submodule (no trailing slash).
    Run rm -rf .git/modules/submodule_name
    Commit
    Delete the now untracked submodule files
    rm -rf path_to_submodule

	

